news.title: Mahindra Group companies run into 'brand' tax
news.para: Mahindra & Mahindra received a notice from the GST office regarding the use of the 'Mahindra' brand name by group companies, questioning why GST wasn't paid for the service between 2017-23.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT posts profit of Rs 37.35 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Brookfield India REIT' adjusted net operating income (NOI) grew by 94% year-on-year from Rs 2,453 million in Q1 FY24 and operating lease rentals grew by 99% year-on-year from Rs 2,113 million in Q1 FY24.

news.title: NatWest Group leases 3.7 lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: The UK banking group said it has leased a new office in Bengaluru with a facility spanning 370,000 sq. ft. over 11 floors, to expand its engineering and innovation hub.

news.title: As many as 50,258 real estate cases pending in consumer courts: Government data
news.para: As per the data, there have been 2,44,813 cases filed in consumer courts at national, state and district levels. Out of that 1,94,555 cases have been disposed and 50,258 cases are pending as on July 31, 2024.

news.title: The Phoenix Mills acquires 9.03 acres land in Coimbatore for Rs 370.17 crore
news.para: Shishir Shrivastava, managing director of The Phoenix Mills said, "We are pleased to announce our acquisition in Coimbatore for a greenfield retail development project."

news.title: NITCO sells four-acre Mumbai plot to Runwal for Rs 232 crore
news.para: The developer is planning to invest Rs 1,500 crore including the land cost to develop a premium residential project on the land parcel.

news.title: Asian Granito India posts profit of Rs 35.36 lakh in Q1 FY25
news.para: Asian Granito India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 343.66 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 0.98 per cent from Rs 340.31 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ajmera Realty issues additional 2% equity shares to its existing shareholders upon de-merger
news.para: The de-merger was approved by NCLT on the July 4, 2024. As per the scheme of arrangement, ARIIL has allotted one equity share with the face value of Rs 10 each against every 50 shares held to its equity shareholders.

news.title: Sobha signs joint develop agreement to construct residential project in Gurugram
news.para: According to the documents accessed through CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm, the deal got registered on July 12 and Sobha has paid Rs 4.3 crore stamp duty for the transaction.

news.title: Gurugram DM orders residents to vacate another 'unsafe' tower of Chintels Paradiso
news.para: The orders were issued by Yadav, who is also the Deputy Commissioner, under Section 163 of Indian Civil Defence Code, according to an official release.

news.title: Signatureglobal (India) posts profit of Rs 6.79 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Signatureglobal (India) net consolidated total income stood at Rs 427.98 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 139.23 per cent from Rs 178.90 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Gurugram civic body fines two societies for flouting waste management rules
news.para: The corporation has given 20 days to ensure compliance with SWM rules, otherwise, it will initiate further action. The regulations mandate that the waste generators have to treat their wet waste and recycle their dry waste.

news.title: DLF appoints Mahender Singh as independent director
news.para: In a regulatory filing, the company informed that the board of directors approved, the appointment of Mahender Singh as an independent director for a period of five consecutive years with effect from August 7, 2024.

news.title: Sand dredged from rivers to be allowed to tackle shortfall: Goa environment minister
news.para: Minister Aleixo Sequeira announced the preparation of a draft khazan land management plan to be opened for public suggestions. The marina project remains shelved due to a high court stay order. The government plans dredging rivers for sand and aims to regularize fishermen's houses under CRZ provisions.

news.title: Average sale price in residential segment to grow 5-6% in FY25: ICRA
news.para: The rating agency expects the area sold in the top seven cities in India to increase by 10-12 per cent to 785-800 million square feet in 2024-25. These seven cities are Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR), Delhi-NCR, Bengaluru, Hyderabad, Pune, Kolkata, and Chennai

news.title: China Evergrande Group's liquidators file lawsuit against PwC in Hong Kong
news.para: The lawsuit is part of an ongoing effort to recover creditors' investments after a Hong Kong court in January ordered the liquidation of Evergrande, once China's biggest real estate company.

news.title: House prices in Britain rise by 2.3% in July: Halifax data
news.para: House prices increased by an annual 2.3%, the biggest yearly increase since January. The last time prices rose by more on an annual basis was February 2023 when they rose by 2.5%.

news.title: Delhi HC appoints arbitrator to deal with disputes between Yuvraj Singh, Brilliant Etoile
news.para: ​The high court said the arbitration would take place under the aegis of the Delhi International Arbitration Centre (DIAC) and would abide by its rules and regulations.

news.title: BHIVE Workspace leases 42,000 sq ft space in Bengaluru
news.para: It plans to expand its managed office space portfolio by an additional one million sq ft space during the current financial year. It has already added two to three properties as part of this plan.

news.title: Investor files liquidation petition against China Evergrande's unit
news.para: Vanward, a Shenzhen-listed electric appliance manufacturer, cited a dispute with Evergrande unit Guangzhou Kailong Real Estate over an investment worth 200 million yuan ($27.9 million).
